President Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Republic of South Sudan to attend the ceremony marking the Declaration of the Independence of the Republic of South Sudan on July 9, 2011. The delegation will be led by the Honorable Susan E. Rice, United States Permanent Representative to the United Nations. Other members of the delegation include the Honorable Donald M. Payne, United States Representative from New Jersey, the Honorable Colin L. Powell, Former Secretary of State and Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, and various other officials from the Department of State, the National Security Staff, and USAID. Mr. Ken Hackett, President of Catholic Relief Services, will also be part of the delegation.